│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ **1. Analysis of the Crash**                                                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ *   **Reproducer:** The crash is triggered by `opt -passes=instcombine` on a piece of LLVM IR that involves adding a shifted `ptrtoint` constant to itself.                              │
│     ```llvm                                                                                                                                                                              │
│     @g = external global i8                                                                                                                                                              │
│     define i32 @shl_add_to_shl_constexpr() {                                                                                                                                             │
│       %shl = shl i32 ptrtoint (ptr @g to i32), 1                                                                                                                                         │
│       %add = add i32 %shl, %shl                                                                                                                                                          │
│       ret i32 %add                                                                                                                                                                       │
│     }                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│     ```                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ *   **Root Cause:** The stack trace shows the crash happens in `tryFactorization` at `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp:762`. The assertion `isa<To>(Val)` fails  │
│ in `cast<Instruction>(Op0)`. This means the code is trying to cast a `Value*` to an `Instruction*`, but the `Value` is not an `Instruction`.                                             │
│ *   **Code Path:** The optimization being attempted is `(A << C) + (B << C) -> (A + B) << C`. In the reproducer, the `add` is `%shl + %shl`, which is `(ptrtoint(...) << 1) +            │
│ (ptrtoint(...) << 1)`. Here, `A` and `B` are both `ptrtoint (ptr @g to i32)`. This `ptrtoint` is a `ConstantExpr`, not an `Instruction`, because it operates on a global address.        │
│ *   **The Bug:** The function `tryFactorization` is called by `tryFactorizationFolds`. The code in `tryFactorizationFolds` extracts the operands `Op0` and `Op1` (which are the          │
│ `ptrtoint` expressions in this case) but fails to check if they are `Instruction`s before calling `tryFactorization`. `tryFactorization` then incorrectly assumes they are               │
│ `Instruction`s and crashes on the cast.                                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ **2. Proposed Fix**                                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fix is to prevent `tryFactorization` from being called with non-instruction operands. I will add a check in the calling function, `tryFactorizationFolds`, to ensure that both `Op0` │
│ and `Op1` are `Instruction`s before proceeding with the factorization attempt.                                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The relevant code in `tryFactorizationFolds` is:                                                                                                                                         │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│     if (C0 == C1 &&                                                                                                                                                                      │
│         (isa<Constant>(Op0) || isa<Constant>(Op1) ||                                                                                                                                     │
│          !haveNoCommonUses(Op0, Op1, SQ))) {                                                                                                                                             │
│       if (auto *F =                                                                                                                                                                      │
│               tryFactorization(I, SQ, Builder, BOpcode, Op0, Op1, C0, C1))                                                                                                               │
│         return F;                                                                                                                                                                        │
│     }                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ I will modify this to:                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│     if (C0 == C1 &&                                                                                                                                                                      │
│         (isa<Constant>(Op0) || isa<Constant>(Op1) ||                                                                                                                                     │
│          !haveNoCommonUses(Op0, Op1, SQ))) {                                                                                                                                             │
│       if (isa<Instruction>(Op0) && isa<Instruction>(Op1))                                                                                                                                │
